You noticed.

17:31.100 --> 17:33.700
And two... helping me
to reach my dreams.

17:33.800 --> 17:36.567
Do what it is I love to do,
perform.

17:36.667 --> 17:38.067
Hey, you ever thought about it?

17:38.100 --> 17:40.167
Maybe it's a good thing
you did lose everything.

17:40.267 --> 17:41.567
'Cause now that frees you up...

17:41.667 --> 17:43.567
to do what it is that you
truly love to do.

17:43.667 --> 17:45.533
What is it you've always
wanted to do...

17:45.633 --> 17:48.700
you never got to do, Starman?

17:48.800 --> 17:52.067
No one's really ever asked me
that before.

17:52.167 --> 17:55.300
I mean, when I was a kid,
I always dreamed of being...

17:55.400 --> 17:58.767
an orthopedic surgeon
for exotic birds.

17:58.867 --> 18:03.467
Yeah, well, I'm not really sure
that is a thing, but if it is...

18:03.567 --> 18:05.167
I say go for it, man!

18:05.267 --> 18:09.800
You know what? I finally realize
why it is they call you Starman.

18:09.900 --> 18:12.533
It's not 'cause you make
men stars.

18:12.633 --> 18:16.233
It's because you were born
to be a star... man.

18:18.067 --> 18:20.367
I am so sorry that I tried
to shoot you...

18:20.467 --> 18:22.200
in the face with a harpoon gun.

18:22.300 --> 18:24.200
It ain't the first time.

18:24.300 --> 18:26.700
You are a great man.

18:29.600 --> 18:36.300
And maybe someday,
if the stars align...

18:36.400 --> 18:39.067
our paths will cross again.

18:41.733 --> 18:44.133
Okay, see you later, man!

18:47.233 --> 18:49.633
DALE (V.O.): My dad wasn't
around much, either.

18:49.733 --> 18:52.833
I don't even have pictures
of him.

18:52.933 --> 18:57.900
The ones I do have are real
blurry and far away.

19:06.667 --> 19:09.333
Damn, looks like we missed
the parade.

19:09.433 --> 19:13.067
Sorry about that and sorry
about your grandma.

19:13.100 --> 19:14.433
No, it's cool.

19:14.533 --> 19:16.233
If she wouldn't have ditched
town, I might not have gotten...

19:16.333 --> 19:19.233
to see your crazy ex-manager
try to harpoon you.

19:19.333 --> 19:20.967
That mean you had fun?

19:21.067 --> 19:24.100
Maybe. Hanging out with you
is certainly never boring.

19:24.200 --> 19:26.767
Hey, I gotta go apologize to
these guys. You gonna be okay?

19:26.867 --> 19:29.200
Yeah.
Be right back.

19:35.200 --> 19:39.133
Hey, guys, sorry I missed
the parade. I took a wrong turn.

19:39.233 --> 19:43.633
It's over? you guys gotta tell
me these things.

19:43.733 --> 19:46.867
I know how bad you wanted
to win.

19:46.967 --> 19:54.933
Well, the Lord truly does work
in mysterious ways.

19:55.067 --> 19:57.633
Laura Beth... did you steal
that?

19:57.733 --> 19:59.900
It turns out that First
Methodist has been hiring...

20:00.000 --> 20:02.900
the Rose Bowl guys to build
their floats all these years.

20:03.000 --> 20:07.100
They were disqualified.
Isn't that great!

20:07.200 --> 20:08.767
I still don't understand
how we won...

20:08.867 --> 20:10.133
if we didn't have a float
in the parade.

20:10.233 --> 20:11.800
Oh, I showed the judges
a picture of the whale...

20:11.900 --> 20:13.300
that I had on my phone.

20:13.400 --> 20:16.533
They said it looked good enough
and they were "over it"...

20:16.633 --> 20:18.300
and they just wanted
to go have lunch.

20:18.400 --> 20:20.400
So, we're gonna go back to the
rectory for some celebratory...

20:20.500 --> 20:25.067
punch and some refreshments,
maybe some scones. Who knows?

20:25.167 --> 20:27.667
That's awesome! All right.
Whoo!

20:30.300 --> 20:33.500
Anyway, you kids don't get
too wild now, have fun.

20:33.600 --> 20:34.567
Thanks, thank you.
I'm proud of you.

20:34.667 --> 20:38.133
Thank you, Pastor Johnson.

20:39.100 --> 20:41.400
Lord have mercy.

20:43.433 --> 20:47.933
Well, now that that's over,
I got the rest of the day free.

20:48.033 --> 20:50.700
I know Ruthie promised you a
trip to New York...

20:50.800 --> 20:55.200
so if you like, maybe I could
drive you instead.

20:55.300 --> 20:58.033
I mean, especially since now
you call me "Dad" and all.

20:58.133 --> 21:02.367
I have no idea what you're
talking about.

21:02.467 --> 21:06.233
Aw, how'd you find that?

21:06.333 --> 21:08.800
It wasn't too hard, because
it was so obviously placed...

21:08.900 --> 21:10.467
on the driver's seat
for me to find.

21:10.567 --> 21:13.067
The worst part was trying to get
it through the blow hole.

21:13.100 --> 21:17.600
Mm, always is.
You gonna listen to it?

21:17.700 --> 21:19.500
I'll put it in my queue.

21:19.600 --> 21:22.433
Be sure and check out track
three.

21:22.533 --> 21:25.067
Duly noted.

21:26.733 --> 21:29.667
( MUSIC PLAYING )

21:29.767 --> 21:32.200
Agh!

21:45.333 --> 21:47.067
I know you didn't see
the first two...

21:47.133 --> 21:49.067
but are you able to follow along
with what's going on here?

21:49.100 --> 21:50.400
I've somehow managed.

21:50.500 --> 21:51.600
( FLESH TEARING )

21:51.700 --> 21:53.533
Holy Jesus! Kicked his head
clean off!
